  "commentary": "With SPX at 6832 sitting just below the 6838 flip point in PIN regime, dealers are currently positioned as stabilizers and likely buying this modest dip given the -0.9% 1-minute move. The massive +6325.9M gamma wall at 6900 creates a strong ceiling where dealer selling pressure intensifies, while the thick positive gamma cluster from 6850-6875 should provide solid support and dampen volatility in this zone. Watch for mean reversion behavior with 6838 as the pivot - breaks above should face increasing headwinds into 6850-6900, while any deeper selling finds natural buying interest around 6700 where dealers flip to supportive mode.\n\nBottom line: expect choppy, range-bound trading between 6800-6900 with a slight upward bias toward the gamma wall.",
